description.p:
A pipe joint of the present invention is a pipe joint for connecting a pipe with a connection opening of a body to be connected comprising;

a fitting connected to an end portion of the pipe and provided with a communication passage communicating into the pipe;

a flange having a through hole into which said fitting is suitable to be inserted, said flange pressingly holding said fitting inserted into said through hole towards said body;

a tightening means for fixing tightly said flange to said body;

an O-ring for sealing a connecting portion of said fitting and said body externally; and

an insertion opening formed in said flange for inserting said tightening means; wherein

a metal seal is provided between said fitting and said body so as to seal a joined portion of said communication passage and said connection opening externally,

said metal seal is composed of a ring member having a "C" shaped cross section, which includes an opening groove in an inner circumference;

said O-ring comprises a first O-ring provided between said fitting and said flange, and

a second O-ring provided between said flange and said body;

a projecting portion is formed on a facing surface of said flange which is opposed to said body, said projecting portion is formed at an area opposite to an area, where said through hole into which the fitting is inserted is formed, with respect to a center axis of said insertion opening, said projection portion projects from said facing surface of said flange towards said body; and

a tip of said fitting inserted into said through hole projects towards said body from said face of said flange.

claim.claim-text:
A pipe joint for connecting a pipe (2) with a connection opening (3a) of a body (3) to be connected comprising;

a fitting (10) connected to an end portion of the pipe (2) and provided with a communication passage (11) communicating into the pipe (2);

a flange (20) having a through hole (21) into which said fitting (10) is suitable to be inserted, said flange (20) pressingly holding said fitting (10) inserted into said through hole (21) towards said body (3);

a tightening means (30) for fixing tightly said flange (20) to said body (3);

an O-ring for sealing a connecting portion of said fitting (10) and said body (3) externally; and

an insertion opening (22) formed in said flange (20) for inserting said tightening means (30);

characterized in that

a metal seal (40) is provided between said fitting (10) and said body (3) so as to seal a joined portion of said communication passage (11) and said connection opening (3a) externally;

said metal seal (40) is composed of a ring member having a "C" shaped cross section, which includes an opening groove (41) in an inner circumference;

said O-ring comprises a first O-ring (50) provided between said fitting (10) and said flange (20), and

a second O-ring (60) provided between said flange (20) and said body (3);

a projecting portion (24) is formed on a facing surface (23) of said flange (20) which is opposed to said body (3), said projecting portion (24) is formed at an area opposite to an area, where said through hole (21) into which the fitting (10) is inserted is formed, with respect to a center axis of said insertion opening (22), said projection portion (24) projects from said facing surface (23) of said flange (20) towards said body (3); and

a tip of said fitting (10) inserted into said through hole (21) projects towards said body (3) from said face of said flange (20).
